ENTRY       EC 2.1.1.291                Enzyme
NAME        (R,S)-reticuline 7-O-methyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Methyltransferases
SYSNAME     S-adenosyl-L-methionine:(R,S)-reticuline 7-O-methyltransferase
REACTION    (1) S-adenosyl-L-methionine + (S)-reticuline = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + (S)-laudanine [RN:R10605];
            (2) S-adenosyl-L-methionine + (R)-reticuline = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + (R)-laudanine [RN:R10606]
ALL_REAC    R10605 R10606;
            (other) R08787 R08788
SUBSTRATE   S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            (S)-reticuline [CPD:C02105];
            (R)-reticuline [CPD:C05178]
PRODUCT     S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine [CPD:C00021];
            (S)-laudanine [CPD:C20712];
            (R)-laudanine [CPD:C09555]
COMMENT     The enzyme from the plant Papaver somniferum (opium poppy) methylates (S)- and (R)-reticuline with equal efficiency and is involved in the biosynthesis of tetrahydrobenzylisoquinoline alkaloids.
